    Article('1986', '6', 'New Methods for Software Development for Just-in-Time Manufacturing', 'New approaches in prototyping, next-bench involvement, performance modeling, and project management created a high-quality software product in the absence of standards or existing systems ', ['Robert A. Passell', 'Raj K. Bhargava', 'Teri L. Lombardi', 'Alvina Y. Nishimoto'], '11-18', '', ''),
    Article('1986', '6', 'The Role of Doppler Ultrasound in Cardiac Diagnosis', 'In ultrasound imaging, a pulse of acoustic energy is transmitted into the human body and the strengths of the returning echoes from various organs and tissues are used to form an image on a display screen. Further information about blood flow and movement can be gained by measuring the shifts in the frequency of the echoes', ["Raymond G. O'Connell Jr"], '20-25', '', ''),
    Article('1986', '6', 'Doppler Effect: History and Theory', 'Data about blood flow anomalies can be obtained by observing the shift in frequency of ultrasonic imaging pulse echoes', ['Paul A. Magnin'], '26-31', '', ''),
    Article('1986', '6', 'Power and Intensity Measurements for Ultrasonic Doppler Imaging Systems', 'Carefully controlling the acoustic energy transmitted into the human body requires accurate analysis methods', ['James Chen'], '31-34', '', ''),
    Article('1986', '6', 'Extraction of Blood Flow Information Using Doppler-Shifted Ultrasound', 'Frequency shifts in ultrasonic echoes are detected by means of specially designed filters and a quadrature sampler', ['Karl E. Thiele', 'Leslie I. Halberg'], '35-40', '', ''),
    Article('1986', '6', 'Continuous-Wave Doppler Board', '', ['Rich Jundanian'], '37', '', ''),
    Article('1986', '6', 'Observation of Blood Flow and Doppler Sample Volume', '', ['Al Tykulsky'], '39', '', ''),
    Article('1986', '6', 'Modifying an Ultrasound Imaging Scanner for Doppler Measurements', 'Changes in timing, more precise focusing, processing enhancements, and power-limiting software had to be developed', ['Sydney M. Karp'], '41-44', '', ''),
    Article('1986', '6', 'Digital Processing Chain for a Doppler Ultrasound Subsystem', 'Time-domain quadrature samples are converted into a gray-scale spectral frequency display using a fast Fourier transform, moment calculations, and digital filtering', ['David C. Hempstead', 'Barry F. Hunt', 'Steven C. Leavitt'], '45-48', '', ''),
    Article('1986', '7', "Cover: HP's briefcase-portable computers: The Portable and the Portable Plus", '', '', '', '', ''),
    Article('1986', '7', "Design of HP's Portable Computer Family", 'The Portable and Portable Plus Computers are compact, lightweight, battery-powered personal computers with built-in software and 80-character-line liquid-crystal displays designed for use by professionals who need portable computing capability in their work', ['Courtney Loomis', 'Ella M. Duyck', 'Carl B. Lantz', 'John T. Eaton', 'Clifford B. Cordy Jr', 'James W. Pearson', 'Michael J. Barbour'], '4-13', '', ''),
